[[SECTION]]
TITLE: 3.1.5 Security, Privacy, and Operational Hardening -> 93_quality_security_traceability_governance.sdoc

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
Security and operational hardening are cross-cutting. Detailed security, privacy, source-of-truth, and traceability governance requirements belong in 93_quality_security_traceability_governance.sdoc. Runtime and deployment details connect to 80_runtime_platform_and_operations.sdoc.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SRS-NFR-SEC-001
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Security Hardening Direction
STATEMENT: >>>
GHOST shall support security hardening around secret discipline, backend exposure reduction, input-boundary hardening, dependency and image hygiene, security-relevant event logging, and operational verification checks.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SRS-NFR-SEC-002
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Context and Memory Control
STATEMENT: >>>
GHOST shall keep selected context, memory reuse, stored memory, excluded information, and model-bound information under explicit engineering control and human-visible inspection.
<<<

[[/SECTION]]

