Memory retrieval, runtime compression, and MemoryMerge synthesis exist, but final Direct Recall priority, memory-context inclusion policy, and final Prompt Builder/send-boundary behavior remain open until approved child requirements define them.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: GHOST-SRS-FR-MEM-005
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: ActiveRetrievalBrief and Blackboard Boundary
STATEMENT: >>>
GHOST shall preserve ActiveRetrievalBrief as part of the memory-management direction, while Blackboard memory hooks shall remain future/reserved unless later requirements and implementation evidence define durable product behavior.
<<<

